React Hook Form wouldn't validate the form unless you register the fields via `useForm` hook and specify the validation rules. So please make sure that:

- You wrap your form with `useForm()` hook.

- You register the inputs via `register` method in the form with validation rules.

Here is an example code snippet with two required fields `firstName` and `lastName`:

```
import { useForm } from "react-hook-form";

function App() {
  const { register, handleSubmit, formState: { errors } } = useForm();
  const onSubmit = data => console.log(data);

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>
      <div>
        <label>First Name</label>
        <input {...register("firstName", { required: true })} />
        {errors.firstName && <span>This field is required</span>}
      </div>
      <div>
        <label>Last Name</label>
        <input {...register("lastName", { required: true })} />
        {errors.lastName && <span>This field is required</span>}
      </div>
      <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>
  );
}
```

Please note that `handleSubmit` will also trigger validation and call the `onSubmit` function only if the form inputs are valid. So if you submit the form without touching any inputs, it will skip validation and directly call the `onSubmit` function.

